I am coming from an S10 which has served me incredibly well for the past 5 years but I wanted a bigger screen because my sight isn't what it used to be. I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. The gain in screen size, even compared to the standard S10, isn't that big of a deal and cannot justify the overall size and bulk.  I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.

About this item    DYNAMIC ISLAND COMES TO IPHONE 15 — Dynamic Island bubbles up alerts and Live Activities — so you don’t miss them while you’re doing something else. You can see who’s calling, check your flight status and so much more.    NNOVATIVE DESIGN — iPhone 15 features a durable colour-infused glass and aluminium design. NEXT-GENERATION PORTRAITS — Capture portraits with dramatically more detail and colour. Just tap to shift the focus between subjects — even after you take the shot.    POWERHOUSE A16 BIONIC CHIP — The superfast chip powers advanced features like computational photography, fluid Dynamic Island transitions and Voice Isolation for phone calls. And A16 Bionic is incredibly efficient to help deliver great all-day battery life.    USB-C CONNECTIVITY — The USB-C connector lets you charge your Mac or iPad with the same cable you use to charge iPhone 15. You can even use iPhone 15 to charge Apple Watch or AirPods.    VITAL SAFETY FEATURES — If you need emergency services and you don’t have mobile service or Wi-Fi, you can use Emergency SOS via satellite.4 With Crash Detection, iPhone can detect a serious car crash and call for help if you can’t.    
   DESIGNED TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE — iPhone comes with privacy protections that help keep you in control of your data. It’s made from more recycled materials to minimise environmental impact. And it has built-in features that make iPhone more accessible to all. [{'Reviewer': 'Alex Beyer', 'Rating': '4.0 ', 'Date': 'Reviewed in the United States on 9 April 2024', 'Review': 'I've only owned every version of the Note series (now Ultra) since Note 4 (did not own the bendy screen one, just regular). Just bring back MicroSD expansion as well. I would say bring back headphones but apparently Android 10 or later killed external mic support via the combo jack. So, that's useless. This was the MAJOR reason why I upgraded my S23 Ultra, no joke, now I can put actual screen protectors on it, don't have to worry about optical glue-on glass that you then cure with UV.Cons:-Love that you can't turn off really annoying unnecessary notifications like the DAILYWELLNESS nonsense, weekly usage reports, "hey we turned these apps off since you're not using them".-Love that the galaxy store now has push notification ads that you can't turn off in settings or in app. That's super cool. Save that crap for your GALAXY A lines that are budget oriented, not your professional S lines.-New S Pen, now most of the time, the S-Pens that come with these are SERVICEABLE at best, but for whatever reason, this year's is painful to use, could be old age kicking in at 36 or just a bad design. It's too thin and too square. Last year's was slightly wider. NEVER MIND, just compared them, they're basically the same, it's the fact that last years had a rubberized texture on it, where this year's is just plastic, that's why it hurts to use.Meh:-A lot of this is more the same incremental improvements; cpu is beefier, display is brighter and more betterer, s pen is faster, touch is faster, etc. THE BORING STUFF.Overall:You always take a gamble with Amazon's "USED" stuff, and was worried that I was going to get a bad one. I bought, USED VERY GOOD, which usually means cosmetic damage somewhere on the device, and then it was "USED VERY GOOD, potentially without box". Mine looked pristine, slapped a screen protector and case on it right away to keep it that way, and it came with a box. You buy this phone if Samsung and styluses are your jam. OTHERWISE there's no real reason to get this. When there are a lot of companies with the 8 Gen 3 out there for a lot cheaper and in smaller more manageable body sizes. If you edit each image one by one on an appropriate editor (not the built in one), you can get the images to look pretty good but a typical iphone 15 takes the same looking image without any editing. I do believe all but the signal issue can be fixed with an update but that would require Samsung to admit there's an issue and then address it which seems to be difficult for them to do. The phone is worth buying simply for the antireflection. It's THAT BIG of a difference. I cannot understand why this isn't getting more attention. Because the network bands in the phone itself are less, and they are specified for Indian networks.Before you open the box, check the "model" number (not the IMEI or serial number). Title: Apple iPhone 15 Pro Max Sim (256 GB) - Natural Titanium
Description:
About this item    FORGED IN TITANIUM — iPhone 15 Pro Max has a strong and light aerospace-grade titanium design with a textured matt-glass back. It also features a super-tough Ceramic Shield front. And it’s splash, water and dust resistant.    ADVANCED DISPLAY — The 6.7 Super Retina XDR display2 with ProMotion ramps up refresh rates to 120Hz when you need exceptional graphics performance. Dynamic Island bubbles up alerts and Live Activities. Plus, with Always-On display, your Lock Screen stays glanceable, so you don’t have to tap it to stay in the know.    GAME-CHANGING A17 PRO CHIP — A Pro-class GPU makes mobile games feel so immersive, with rich environments and realistic characters. A17 Pro is also incredibly efficient and helps to deliver amazing all-day battery life.    POWERFUL PRO CAMERA SYSTEM — Get incredible framing flexibility with 7 pro lenses. Capture super high resolution photos with more colour and detail using the 48MP Main camera. And take sharper close-ups from further away with the 5x Telephoto camera on iPhone 15 Pro Max.    CUSTOMISABLE ACTION BUTTON — Action button is a fast track to your favourite feature. Just set the one you want, like Silent mode, Camera, Voice Memo, Shortcut and more. Then press and hold to launch the action.    PRO CONNECTIVITY — The new USB-C connector lets you charge your Mac or iPad with the same cable you use to charge iPhone 15 Pro Max. With USB 3, you get a huge leap in data transfer speeds.4 And you can download files up to 2x faster using Wi-Fi 6E.    VITAL SAFETY FEATURES — If you need emergency services and you don’t have mobile service or Wi-Fi, you can use Emergency SOS via satellite.6 With Crash Detection, iPhone can detect a serious car crash and call for help if you can’t.

From lag-free gaming to seamless multitasking, experience the cutting-edge capabilities of this chipset.    ☆【Battery】:- 5000 mAh Battery || Power up at lightning speed with the 67 W SUPERVOOC Charge and revel in extended usage with the robust 5000 mAh battery. Stay connected longer with reduced wait times. The dual charge pump technology and intelligent five-core chip protection ensure optimal charging efficiency and top-tier device safety.    ☆【Display Other Features】:- 60Hz/90Hz/120Hz Refresh Rate, Aspect Ratio: 20.1:9, Screen-to-Body Ratio: 93%, 240Hz Touch Sampling Rate, Screen Contrast: 5000000:1, Maximum Brightness: 500 nits, Color Saturation: DCI-P3 100%, Supports Sunlight Screen, Color Gamut: DCI-P3 100%    ☆【50 MP SONY IMX882 OIS Camera】:- Transform your photography with the realme 12 Pro 5G's pioneering 50 MP SONY IMX882 OIS Camera. Boasting the largest sensor in its segment, this camera crafts unmatched HDR and nightscape brilliance. Bid farewell to blur with SuperOIS, while the Ultra Clarity Engine and DIS Engine ensure unparalleled precision. Elevate your photography game with this game-changing device that captures moments with unprecedented clarity.    
   ☆【32 MP 2X Flagship Telephoto Portrait Camera】:- Embark on a journey of photography excellence, this camera brings 2x optical zoom & 4x lossless zoom to the forefront, delivering superior sharpness, noise control & dynamic range that leaves rivals behind. Setting a new standard for portrait effects in its price range, it takes your photography game to unparalleled heights. ☆【8 GB+8 GB Dynamic RAM】:- Seamlessly multitask with an impressive 8 GB + 8 GB of Dynamic RAM and enjoy ample space for photos, videos, and documents with up to 256 GB of storage. Crafted in collaboration with master watchmaker Ollivier Savelli, this smartphone integrates classic luxury watch elements. Title: Apple iPhone 15 Pro Max (256GB) - Titanium Black
Description:
About this item    Forged from titanium - The iPhone 15 Pro Max has a robust and lightweight design made of space grade titanium with a textured matte glass back. It also has a ceramic shield front that can withstand more than any smartphone glass. And it is protected from water and dust.    Advanced display – The 6.7" Super Retina XDR display with ProMotion increases refresh rates up to 120 Hz when you need a lot of graphics power. Dynamic Island brings notifications and live activities forward. And with the Always On Display, the lock screen always shows your most important information without having to tap it.    ALL CHANGING A17 PRO CHIP – A Pro GPU makes games an immersive experience, with detailed environments and realistic characters. The A17 Pro is incredibly efficient and ensures that you have battery for the whole day.    POWERFUL PRO CAMERA SYSTEM - Incredible flexibility in choosing the image section, as if you had 7 Pro lenses. Take super-high-resolution photos with more colour and detail with the 48MP main camera. And with the 5x Tele camera in the iPhone 15 Pro Max, you can take sharper close-up shots from a greater distance.    Customizable action button - The action button takes you directly to your favourite feature. Simply set mute mode, camera, voice memo, shortcut or other feature. Then all you have to do is press and hold the Action Button to start it.    Pro connectivity - Via the USB C port, you can charge your Mac or iPad with the same cable you use to charge your iPhone 15 Pro Max. With USB 3, you get a huge leap in data transfer.4 And you can load files with Wi-Fi 6E up to 2x faster.    Important safety features - If you need to contact an emergency service but have no network and no WiFi, you can use emergency call SOS via satellite. With accident detection, the iPhone can detect a serious car accident and call for help when you can't.

Read more'}, {'Reviewer': 'Joh M', 'Rating': '5.0 ', 'Date': 'Reviewed in Germany on 19 August 2024', 'Review': 'Nachdem ich zunächst das iPhone 15 Pro hatte, musste ich es leider aufgrund des schwachen Akkus zurückschicken. Der Akku des Pro-Modells hielt bei mir leider nicht einmal einen ganzen Tag durch, was einfach nicht meinen Erwartungen entsprach. Deshalb entschied ich mich, auf das iPhone 15 Pro Max umzusteigen, und ich könnte nicht zufriedener sein.Das iPhone 15 Pro Max überzeugt in allen Bereichen. Der größere Akku war natürlich der Hauptgrund für meinen Wechsel, und er hat mich absolut nicht enttäuscht. Selbst bei intensiver Nutzung hält der Akku problemlos einen ganzen Tag durch, oft sogar länger. Für jemanden wie mich, der das Smartphone ständig nutzt – sei es für Arbeit, Fotografie, oder Streaming – ist die verlängerte Akkulaufzeit ein riesiger Vorteil.Die Kamera des iPhone 15 Pro Max ist schlichtweg beeindruckend. Die Dreifach-Kamera mit dem verbesserten 48-Megapixel-Hauptsensor liefert atemberaubende Fotos, selbst bei schlechten Lichtverhältnissen. Der verbesserte Nachtmodus und die Möglichkeit, in 4K ProRes zu filmen, sind Funktionen, die das Herz jedes Fotografie- und Videografie-Enthusiasten höher schlagen lassen. Die neue 5-fach Telefotokamera bietet zudem noch mehr kreative Möglichkeiten, besonders wenn es darum geht, entfernte Objekte scharf und detailliert festzuhalten.Das 6,7 Zoll große Super Retina XDR Display ist eine wahre Augenweide. Die ProMotion-Technologie mit bis zu 120 Hz sorgt für unglaublich flüssige Animationen und ein butterweiches Scrollen. Egal ob beim Gaming, beim Ansehen von Videos oder beim einfachen Surfen – das Display ist einfach ein Genuss. Die Farben sind lebendig, die Helligkeit ist mehr als ausreichend, und die Kontraste sind gestochen scharf.Ein weiterer großer Pluspunkt ist das neue Titan-Gehäuse, das dem iPhone 15 Pro Max nicht nur ein edles Aussehen verleiht, sondern es auch widerstandsfähiger und zugleich leichter macht. Das Gerät liegt trotz seiner Größe angenehm in der Hand und fühlt sich dabei robust und hochwertig an.Das iPhone 15 Pro Max kommt außerdem mit der neuen A17 Pro-Chip-Architektur, die eine unglaubliche Leistung bietet. Apps starten blitzschnell, Multitasking läuft reibungslos, und selbst grafikintensive Spiele laufen flüssig und ohne Verzögerungen. Die Performance ist wirklich auf einem Niveau, das man sonst nur von High-End-Laptops kennt.Ein weiteres Highlight ist der erweiterte USB-C-Anschluss, der jetzt nicht nur schnelleres Laden ermöglicht, sondern auch vielseitiger in der Datenübertragung ist. Die Datenübertragungsraten sind deutlich schneller als bei früheren Modellen, was besonders nützlich ist, wenn man große Dateien wie 4K-Videos übertragen möchte.Natürlich darf man auch die verbesserten Datenschutz- und Sicherheitsfunktionen nicht vergessen. Apple hat hier wieder einmal neue Maßstäbe gesetzt, und ich fühle mich rundum sicher bei der Nutzung dieses Geräts.Zusammengefasst ist das iPhone 15 Pro Max wirklich das Rundum-Sorglos-Paket. Es bietet alles, was man von einem Premium-Smartphone erwarten kann – und noch mehr. Vom beeindruckenden Display über die leistungsstarke Kamera bis hin zur überragenden Akkulaufzeit und dem eleganten Design – dieses iPhone lässt keine Wünsche offen. Für mich hat sich der Wechsel definitiv gelohnt, und ich kann das iPhone 15 Pro Max uneingeschränkt empfehlen.

Title: realme Realme C51 Dual-SIM 256GB ROM + 6GB RAM 4G (Mint Green) - Middle East Version
Description:
About this item    Stunning Visuals: Immerse yourself in vibrant colors and clarity with the Realme C51's 6.74-inch IPS LCD display, featuring a 90Hz refresh rate and a peak brightness of 560 nits.    Powerful Performance: The smartphone runs on Android 13 with Realme UI T, powered by the Unisoc Tiger T612 chipset, octa-core CPU, and Mali-G57 GPU, ensuring seamless multitasking and smooth navigation.    Ample Storage: Enjoy 256GB of storage paired with 6GB of RAM, and expand your storage further with the microSDXC slot for additional convenience.    Capture Every Moment: The Realme C51 boasts a dual rear camera setup, including a 50 MP primary camera with a wide aperture and a 0.08 MP depth sensor for artistic bokeh effects. Record your favorite moments in 1080p at 30fps.    Connectivity and Convenience: Stay connected with Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, Bluetooth 5.0, and NFC (market/region dependent). The USB Type-C 2.0 port with OTG support facilitates easy data transfer, and a 3.5mm audio jack allows for uninterrupted music enjoyment.    Security and Sensors: Your data is secure with the side-mounted fingerprint sensor. The Realme C51 features various sensors, including an accelerometer, proximity sensor, and compass.    All-Day Battery: The smartphone is equipped with a 5000 mAh non-removable Li-Po battery, providing all-day power. Additionally, the 33W wired charging allows you to reach 50% battery in just 28 minutes (advertised).    
   Sleek Design: The Realme C51 combines power with style, available in Mint Green and Carbon Black to suit your personal aesthetic. Affordable Excellence: Packed with features and performance typically found in higher-priced smartphones, the Realme C51 offers unbeatable value, making advanced technology accessible to all. Multimedia Enjoyment: Whether streaming videos, gaming, or browsing, every detail shines through on the Realme C51's high-quality display, ensuring an immersive multimedia experience.
